        <num>CCP 4555</num>
        <heading>4555.  Appeal</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 4555.  Appeal
An appeal from a judgment of interdiction, an order or judgment appointing or removing a curator or undercurator, or a judgment modifying or terminating interdiction shall be taken within thirty days from the applicable date provided by Article 2087.  The order or judgment is not suspended during the pendency of an appeal. The acts of a curator or an undercurator shall not be invalidated by the annulment of his appointment on appeal.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
